As the crackdown of non compliant matatu’s enters day 3, K24 has learnt that the biggest impediment to the restoration of sanity in the sector, is the very same people mandated to enforce law. Police officers, some of who own fleets of matatus. Sources within the police has told K24 that this has become a thorn in the flesh of the National Police Service as this officers who taken an oath to enforce the law become agents of lawlessness. This as confusion reigns in the sector as to the what compliance with the Michuki rules means.  